WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.000
results of the photo competition.

00:04.000 --> 00:10.000
Tonight I am more than happy to read out the winners of the photo competition.

00:10.000 --> 00:14.000
We were very pleased with our competition this year.

00:14.000 --> 00:19.000
Compared with other years, we received many more photos.

00:19.000 --> 00:27.000
Even though all of the photos are excellent, we are sorry to say that we cannot give prizes to everyone.

00:27.000 --> 00:35.000
The person who won the prize for the subject nature is 15-year-old Lee Wei.

00:35.000 --> 00:41.000
Lee Wei took a photo of the trees in Sian Shan Park.

00:41.000 --> 00:46.000
His photo shows the different colours on the hill.

00:46.000 --> 00:54.000
The photo which we liked best in the city and people group was taken by Chao Min.

00:54.000 --> 00:58.000
Chao Min is only 12 years old.

00:58.000 --> 01:04.000
Her photo shows a person rushing across a street on a windy evening.

01:04.000 --> 01:13.000
It is a beautiful girl who is wearing a blouse and skirt and who is protecting her books against the showers.

01:13.000 --> 01:19.000
The best photo in the music group was taken by her Chao Min.

01:19.000 --> 01:28.000
His photo of the group Crazy Feet shows the singer Becky Wong and the band playing at a concert.

01:28.000 --> 01:39.000
Her Jong manages to show how this great new band moves and sounds and the good time which their fans are having.

01:40.000 --> 01:49.000
A group of photos which show Beijing and Cambridge in England has won the prize for the subject Home and Away.

01:49.000 --> 01:57.000
They show some of the experiences of a young visitor to our country and some memories of his home.

01:57.000 --> 02:01.000
The winner is Tony Smith.

02:01.000 --> 02:07.000
Congratulations to our winners and thanks to everyone who entered the competition.

02:07.000 --> 02:14.000
Now let's welcome our headmaster to present the prizes to the winners.

